{{orphan | date = May 2011}}

'''Glomar Challenger Basin''' ({{coord|77|45|S|180|0|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a northeast trending [[Oceanic basin|undersea basin]] in the central [[Ross Sea]] [[continental shelf]] named for the research ship ''[[Glomar Challenger]]''. The name was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1988.<ref name=gnis/>

